Senator Carl Levin, a Democrat from Michigan, expressed his support for the American Jobs Act proposed by President Obama in a statement following the president's address to Congress. He called it a patriotic call for bipartisan action and emphasized that the program outlined by the president would help accelerate economic recovery without adding to the budget deficit. Levin also highlighted the bipartisan support that similar elements of the program have had in the past. He stressed the importance of Congress working together to create jobs, particularly for the people of Michigan and the nation. Levin expressed hope that his Republican colleagues would join in this effort.